            <p>Initially this framework doesn't need to check
            revocation or certificate issuer, just check the
            response from the client and confirm it matches the
            expected value based on the public key..</p>
            <p>There may already be frameworks available, in which
            case we should not emulate their functionality. This is
            more a PoC than anything else, and proves that we can,
            in fact, accomplish client certificate authentication.
            Reimplementing anything, particularly anything
            cryptography-related, is just a Bad Idea.</p>
